    "The mathematical formalism of background-averaged epistasis handling binary genetic sequences (with a maximum of two alleles per position) [54] relies on the Walsh-Hadamard transform [55,56] but has been recently extended to handle genetic landscapes of arbitrary shape and complexity [33,57].",
